TRAVEL INFORMATION
Make your reservations as far in advance as possible. SUNWORLD requests that passengers
check-in at the boarding gate at least 30 minutes before scheduled departure time, but must be
at the SUNWORLD boarding gate 10 minutes before scheduled departure or the reservation will
be subject to cancellation.
Provide SUNWORLD personnel a phone number where you can be reached at your boarding
station. Should a change in your plans necessitate cancellation of your flight reservation, please
notify SUNWORLD as soon as possible to permit resale to other passengers.
SCHEDULE
All times shown are local times and all flights operate daily unless indicated otherwise.
Schedules and fares are subject to change without notice.
BAGGAGE REGULATIONS
For each ticketed passenger, the free baggage allowance is two checked bags not over 62 inches
and 55 inches respectively. In addition, carry-on baggage may remain in the passengers
possession and be carried aboard SUNWORLD aircraft provided its dimensions allow storage
beneath a passenger seat or in the overhead compartments. Each additional piece checked will
be $5.00
FAA regulations require all articles carried on-board commercial aircraft to be inspected.

HAZARDOUS MATERIALS
Federal regulations restrict carriage of hazardous materials. These materials include, but are not
limited to, flammable gas, liquids and solids; non-flammable compressed gas; explosives;
poisons, corrosives, oxidizing materials; radioactive materials; etiologic agents and magnetic
materials. These materials, and others, may not be included in carry-on baggage. Violators are
subject to substantial fines.
RESERVATIONS POLICY
SUNWORLD will selectively overbook certain flights to compensate for persons holding and not
utilizing reservations, thus making available more seats for those persons actually seeking them.
As a result, there is a slight chance that a seat may not be available for a person holding a
confirmed reservation. SUNWORLD will offer alternate transportation and compensation as
provided in its applicable contract of carriage.
SUNWORLD is not responsible for lost tickets.
